## What Went Well

1. **Histogram Visualization** - Clear km distribution chart with fleet average line and target range highlighting

2. **Outlier Detection** - Automatic identification of trains >15% off average with recommended actions

3. **Scenario Sandbox** - What-if scenarios correctly isolate changes from production data

4. **Simulation Performance** - Results return in <10 seconds per NFR-1.4 requirement

5. **Comparison View** - Side-by-side metrics with best-value highlighting enables informed decisions

---

## Challenges Encountered

1. **Chart Library Selection** - Evaluated multiple charting libraries before settling on lightweight solution

2. **Simulation State Management** - Tracking scenario changes without affecting production required careful state isolation

3. **Projection Algorithm** - 30-day km projection needed assumptions about future service patterns

4. **UI Complexity** - Balancing page has many interactive elements; required careful layout design

---

## Lessons Learned

1. **Visualization First** - Starting with histogram design helped clarify data requirements

2. **Simulation Isolation** - Clear visual indicator ("Scenario Mode") essential to prevent user confusion

3. **Progressive Disclosure** - Show summary first, details on demand; keeps interface manageable

4. **Comparison Limits** - 2-3 scenario comparison maximum; more becomes visually overwhelming

